@400511 = ~Buckler +2~
@400512 = ~This legendary buckler was the property of Kenstrel of Baldur's Gate. A trickster and member of the thieves' guild, it is said that he swindled it off a band of travelling adventurers, 'demonstrating' it to be cursed and an omen of bad luck that would follow them wherever they went. After the third time their inn was invaded by scores of hideous, badger-like creatures, causing significant damage to the establishment, along with other mishaps that began to plague their lives, they eventually agreed to hand it over for Kenstrel to rid it of its curse, which unsurprisingly was the last they ever saw of him.

STATISTICS:

Armor Class: +3, +4 vs missiles

Weight: 2
